p: GC-MS analysis was also performed with a different sample preparation approach consisting in saponification and subsequent extraction by dispersive liquid-liquid microextraction (DLLME) of EPP, in order to analyse the most lipophilic compounds. This analysis mostly confirmed the presence of several already identified compounds ( Table 2), such as: phytol (53.85%), fucosterol (17.57%), palmitic acid (12.00%), cholesterol (4.57%), 2,4-di-tert-butylphenol (2.99%), stearic acid (3.40%), oleic acid (0.59%), dihydroactinidiolide (0.62%), squalene (0.19%) and Î´-tocopherol (0.27%), and n-nonadecanol-1 (0.20%).
